buildings.name: Teacher's Education Building
buildings.description: The Teacherâ€™s Education Building houses programs focused on developing future educators and instructional leaders. It includes lecture rooms, micro-teaching laboratories, curriculum resource centers, and faculty offices. The building supports training in teaching methodologies, classroom management, educational technology, and field demonstration activities. It is a hub for aspiring teachers preparing for Licensure Examination for Teachers (LET) competency.

buildings.name: Engineering Building
buildings.description: The Engineering Building is dedicated to programs in computer, electronics, electrical, and other applied engineering fields. It features specialized laboratories such as circuits labs, computer labs, workshop areas, and innovation spaces. Students conduct hands-on experiments, prototype development, and technical research here. The building also hosts most engineering lectures, faculty offices, and project-based learning sessions.
